comments.content: I'm making a snap call, but it looks like Clarendon.

Closer to Clarendon Condensed Bold: [http://www.myfonts.com/fonts/bitstream/clarendon/bold-condensed/](http://web.archive.org/web/20100309130710/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/bitstream/clarendon/bold-condensed/ "http://www.myfonts.com/fonts/bitstream/clarendon/bold-condensed/")

Hard to tell with the image sideways.
I used to use Rosewood Fill for tons of projects in college. I forgot what the appeal was for me.

Rosewood rocks... but... why is this post handpicked?
